      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model choice (bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V) justified by literature and confirmed by coupon-level calibration; contact formulation validated against known analytical solutions.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (E=114 GPa, sigma_y=880 MPa, E_t=2.2 GPa) reproduces tensile coupon stress-strain data to within 3% across the plastic regime. Augmented Lagrange contact with friction coefficient 0.25 (measured by pin-on-disk) selected after comparison with frictionless and penalty-only formulations. Model form uncertainty quantified and included in total uval."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material and geometric inputs traceable to measurements or qualified literature; input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (N=500) and reported as part of uval.",
      "rationale": "Material properties drawn from internal characterization dataset (DSM-2025-0341; dataVintage 2025-08-22). Geometric dimensions measured from three production screws via CMM (±0.005 mm). Input uncertainty propagated via Latin Hypercube sampling (N=500 runs). Combined input uncertainty contribution to stiffness QoI: ±4.1 N/mm (1-sigma). The material dataset predates the September 2025 mesh-refinement model revision by approximately three weeks; the revision affected cortical shell element formulation only and was judged by the analysis team to be immaterial to material property applicability, so no re-characterization was performed."
    },
    {
